Half Subtractor

A Half Subtractor is a combinational logic circuit used to subtract two single-bit binary numbers. 
It has two inputs (A and B) and produces two outputs: Difference and Borrow. 
The Difference output is generated using the XOR operation, while the Borrow output is generated using NOT and AND operations.

Full Subtractor

A Full Subtractor is a combinational logic circuit used to subtract three binary bits, 
including the borrow input from the previous stage. It has three inputs (A, B, and Bin) and produces two outputs: Difference and Borrow Out.
Full Subtractors are widely used in digital systems and arithmetic operations
